# 1. 久しぶりのオフ！

Minori: Phew...
Minori: Today was really fun! It's been so long since I got to stay all day for classes!
Minori: But I can't let my guard down...! We've got tests coming up, so I'll need to review what we went over today once I get home.
Haruka: Hi, Minori. Are you ready to head over for our meeting today?
Minori: Oh! Hi, Haruka!
Minori: We're discussing what we're gonna do moving forward, right?! I'm so excited. It feels like it's been forever since we last met up on the rooftop♪
Haruka: Hehe. Me too. We've been so busy with work lately that it's been rare for all four of us to be at school together.
Haruka: We have the MORE MORE HOUSE now... But the rooftop is where everything began for us, so I'm hoping that we can keep coming back from time to time.
Minori: Me too! Both the MORE MORE HOUSE and the rooftop mean so much to us, so...
???: Hey, you two!
Minori: Oh, Kaepon...! And with most of our class!
Classmate: Long time no see, you two. We know you've been busy, but is everything okay?
Haruka: Yes, we're grateful that we've been getting so many offers.
Minori: You've been showing up in so many magazines, Kaepon! You looked so pretty in the latest issue of “uou-ou”.
Kaepon: Thanks! Along with uou-ou, I've been doing a ton of shoots for a bunch of different magazines lately.
Kaepon: But enough about me! I saw you girls on “Chat A Lot About Nothing with Takashi Arimura!”
Minori: Wait, Kaepon, you watched...?!
Kaepon: Of course I watched! I mean, I knew that my friends were gonna be on it!
Classmate: Same here! I still can't believe that you all got to be on such a famous person's primetime program!
Haruka: Actually, we got pretty lucky there. The group that was originally slated to go on had to cancel suddenly, and we were asked to fill in for them.
Minori: The producer just happened to be someone we had worked with earlier, and they were kind enough to give us a chance.
Kaepon: Wow, really...?! I guess it goes to show how important it is to have connections!
Kaepon: Anyway, I loved it, and I doubt it could've gone better! I even overheard some girls talking about it when I stopped by the school store earlier.
Haruka: Now that you mention it, this might be the biggest response we've gotten so far.
Minori: Yeah! Our name recognition's really been going up, so moving forward...
Minori: Whoa, look at the time!
Minori: Sorry, everyone! We've gotta get to a meeting...!
Kaepon: Actually, I've gotta run to the studio too! Sorry, I didn't mean to keep you two like this.
Classmate: But I'm really glad we got to talk. Tell us more when you have some more free time!
Minori: We will. Bye bye!
Haruka: Alright, shall we head up to the rooftop?
Minori: Yeah! That was a nice boost of encouragement.
Minori: So we gotta keep doing our best!
Airi: Alright, now that we've all had a chance to report on our activities, I'd like for us to start discussing stream ideas next. But...
Minori: But?
Airi: I still can't believe how much everyone's been talking about that show.
Minori: Oh, Airi, you feel the same way...?!
Haruka: We actually just got to chat with our classmates about it.
Shizuku: While walking through the courtyard, I had some girls call out to me and say, “We loved that show! We're rooting for you!”
Shizuku: Some girls I haven't had a chance to talk to lately even sent me messages saying how they saw us on that show...
Shizuku: It's so nice to see how we're able to reach more people than ever now.
Airi: Hehe. Sounds like we all feel the same way.
Airi: To be fair, we have to thank our lucky stars for getting a chance to appear on that show. There's no guarantee that we're going to keep receiving such big offers...
Airi: However, there's no arguing that we've reached a turning point.
Minori: A turning point...?
Haruka: I agree. On top of us rising up the trend charts, we've been getting more and more new people following us.
Haruka: This means we'll need to consider their needs with regards to our streams since they're just starting to get to know us.
Minori: R-Right...!
Shizuku: So, for our next stream, should we come up with ways to tell our new viewers what we're doing and such...?
Airi: Yeah, but we shouldn't focus all our attention on them. Doing so would lead to us alienating our existing followers...
Minori: Then, let's introduce ourselves to our new viewers while also doing something fun that our existing ones will enjoy!
Haruka: How exactly...?
Minori: Uhh...
Minori: I haven't actually thought it all the way through...
Airi: Big swing and a miss.
Shizuku: But I think I understand what Minori's trying to say.
Shizuku: We should try putting on streams that all our viewers old and new can enjoy.
Haruka: Right.
Haruka: It won't be easy, but let's start coming up with ideas along those lines.
Airi: Yeah, sounds good.
Airi: But we're just about out of time, so let's end today's meeting here.
Shizuku: Oh, right... I have to be somewhere after this.
Shizuku: We'll be having our next meeting at the MORE MORE HOUSE tomorrow, so let's keep thinking about what we talked about today until then.
Airi: Yeah... I'm hoping that we'll be able to get the ball rolling once we've got a few ideas under our belt.
Minori: Coming up with good stream ideas is really hard, but I promise to do my best again this time around...!
Airi: I'll also do my best to come up with something good.
Airi: Anyway, this meeting's adjourned! See you all tomorrow!
Minori: Okay, see you!
